- Efficient irrigation methods suitable for corn are those with a method_id associated with irrigation_methods where suitable_crops contain 'corn'; 
- Average efficiency refers to the average of the water efficiency of the irrigation method; 
- Total irrigated area refers to the total area of the county in acres that has been irrigated; 
- Recent data refers to data from 2015 onwards.

- The most efficient irrigation method refers to the method with the highest average water efficiency; 
- Compliance status 'non-compliant' indicates that the county has had at least one non-compliant report in the last year; 
- A county's compliance status is marked as 0 (compliant) if there are no non-compliant reports in the last year.

;
Note that 'improvement' is interpreted as an increase in efficiency, and 'most recent year' refers to the latest year available in the irrigation_data table; 
A 'non-compliant' county is one with a compliance_status of 'non-compliant' in the most recent compliance reports.

- Irrigation data refers to the total area of land in a county that is watered artificially; 
- Historical and current irrigated areas are the total irrigated areas in past and present, respectively; 
- A county with irrigation data is one that has either historical or current irrigated areas greater than 0.

High irrigation refers to counties with an average total irrigated area greater than 1000 acres; 
Average total irrigated area and average irrigated area under threshold are calculated in acres; 
The data is sorted in descending order, meaning the county with the most extensive average irrigated area will be listed first.
